FOLLOWING the North Gauteng High Court ordering Brian Molefe
to pay back the R11 million he received from Eskom, he might face criminal
charges.Speaking to Fin24, trade union Solidarity chief executive
Dirk Hermann said the next step for the union would be to pursue criminal
charges against Molefe.A full bench at the North Gauteng High Court found that
